Projects Here you'll discover a little of the history of each project I maintain. OSI: Open Source Initiative. This site (yes, this one) üë®üèª‚Äçüé® Have you seen that cool portfolio but have no idea how it was made? My portfolio is open-source and you can not only look at it, but create a fork and adapt it to use in your own portfolio. It also serves as a small showcase of my work in frontend, since most of my projects are focused in backend. wellwelwel/weslley.io License: AGPL-3.0 Node.js JavaScript TypeScript GitHub GitHub Actions Apache Docker Docusaurus MDX React Sass Cloudflare Visual Studio Code Poku üê∑ As a dependency creator, the initial idea was to create a test runner that would truthfully ensure that my projects worked for Node.js, Deno and Bun at the same time, using the same test suite to do so. Then an idea came to me along the way: What if I made testing easy? As result, a zero-configuration test runner has arisen, which goes back to the JavaScript origins and brings back its native syntax essence for tests, plus performing up to 5 times faster than the most popular test runner in the entire JavaScript ecosystem in a simple benchmark. wellwelwel/poku License: MIT Node.js Bun Deno JavaScript TypeScript Bash GitHub GitHub Actions Docker Codecov npm Docusaurus MDX React Sass Algolia Cloudflare Visual Studio Code MySQL2 üê¨ I'm proud to be a maintainer of MySQL2, one of the faster MySQL clients in the entire JavaScript ecosystem and the most downloaded for Node.js, Bun, and Deno, as well as being used by more than 1 million public projects on GitHub. It's the main component behind projects such as Sequelize, Drizzle ORM, TypeORM, Knex, among other frameworks (ORM) for MySQL connections. On March 24, 2024, I migrated the entire MySQL2 test suite to Poku, ensuring compatibility between Node.js, Bun and Deno. sidorares/node-mysql2 License: MIT Node.js Bun Deno JavaScript TypeScript MySQL Amazon Web Services (AWS) Azure Azure SQL Database Cloudflare Workers Bash GitHub GitHub Actions Docker Codecov npm Docusaurus MDX React Sass SVPS: Simplifying VPS üöÄ The original idea was just to automate some personal tasks when I purchased a ‚Äúzeroed‚Äù VPS or EC2, but it ended up becoming an extremely robust ORM for Ubuntu servers. As well as repairing and installing the most commonly used tools on servers in a granular approach, SVPS also enables you to create proxies automatically, directing ports to any domain or subdomain you want. This project is currently one of the main sources of my company's profits. wellwelwel/svps License: MIT Bash Node.js JavaScript TypeScript Linux Apache PHP Composer MySQL Amazon Web Services (AWS) Azure Azure DevOps GitHub GitHub Actions Docker npm Visual Studio Code lru.min üî• A performance investigation that resulted in one of the most performant and consistent LRU-based cache projects in the entire JavaScript ecosystem. It's currently used by more than 170,000 public repositories on GitHub and is downloaded more than 5 million times a month. wellwelwel/lru.min License: MIT Node.js Bun Deno JavaScript TypeScript GitHub GitHub Actions Codecov npm Visual Studio Code AWS SSL Profiles üìú Originated from a confusion after AWS changed all its authentication certificates for RDS services, breaking systems that had been working perfectly for years, this project came about to unify the certificates in one place. This way, any maintainer of a project that depends on these certificates (mysql, mysql2 and pg in particular) no longer has to worry about unexpected updates. Despite its simplicity, it's downloaded more than 6 million times a month. mysqljs/aws-ssl-profiles License: MIT Node.js JavaScript TypeScript MySQL Amazon Web Services (AWS) Azure Azure SQL Database GitHub GitHub Actions npm Packages Update üì¶ After noticing that all the NPM package updaters had several dependencies, as well as megabytes, this project began as a personal challenge to create the same one, but without any dependencies. Today, the project has evolved and is used especially to update monorepositories dynamically, weighing around 40KB in the final total of its installation. wellwelwel/packages-update License: MIT Node.js JavaScript TypeScript GitHub GitHub Actions npm Visual Studio Code Poku Theme üé® A cute "gothic pastel" theme inspired by Poku's test runner visual identity. While Poku test runner makes testing easier, Poku's theme makes it easy to read your code, since it's not just about combining colors, but establishing consistency between different language syntaxes. You can check with your favorite theme if the types in TypeScript and PHP have the same color, because in Poku Theme it will üòè pokujs/themes License: MIT Node.js JavaScript TypeScript GitHub GitHub Actions Visual Studio Code Local Ubuntu VPS and EC2 ‚òòÔ∏è A completely cost-free option for creating VPS, KVM, EC2, and Azure environments locally, perfect for development and testing. Sounds complex, right? But just download the Docker image and use it with everything ready: docker pull wellwelwel/vps. wellwelwel/local-vps-and-ec2 License: MIT Bash Linux Docker Amazon Web Services (AWS) Azure Azure DevOps GitHub GitHub Actions Visual Studio Code There are more! üöß There are A LOT of projects and over time I promise to put each one of them here, but just look at my GitHub and there's everything there.
